'''Yavannië''' ([[Ivanneth]] in [[Sindarin]]) was the ninth month of the year in the [[King's Reckoning]] and the [[Stewards' Reckoning]] of [[Gondor]], following [[Úrimë]], and preceding the month of [[Narquelië]]. In the Stewards' Reckoning, ''Yavannië'' preceded the autumn feast of [[Yáviérë]]. In the [[New Reckoning]], ''Yavannië'' was the sixth month of the year (still following ''Úrimë'') and preceded the New Reckoning's ''[[Enderi]]''.<ref name="D2">{{App|Calendars}}</ref>

''Yavannië'' in the Kings' Reckoning (and for the most part in the Stewards' Reckoning) corresponded to [[Halimath]] in the [[Shire Calendar]]<ref name="D2" /> (approximately modern [[23 August]] through [[21 September]]). In the New Reckoning, 30 Yavannië corresponded with the birthday of [[Frodo Baggins]], [[22 September|22 Halimath]] in the [[Shire Calendar]], and was made a festival.<ref name="D2" />

